1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,369
{\an8}<i>Sianong!</i>

2
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:37,871
{\an8}Sianong.

3
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:39,914
{\an8}What about Alex? Where is he?

4
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:43,126
{\an8}Chiara the Valtrovi?!

5
00:00:47,255 --> 00:00:48,256
{\an8}There it is!

6
00:00:50,049 --> 00:00:51,760
{\an8}It's just beginner's luck.

7
00:00:58,558 --> 00:01:00,435
{\an8}You're so cool!

8
00:01:01,853 --> 00:01:04,147
{\an8}Oh, yes, so much.

9
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:07,067
{\an8}<i>I'm actually worried about Mikoy.</i>

10
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:10,862
{\an8}I didn't know
if he's hiding something from me.

11
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:19,120
{\an8}Do you want fish and chips? Huh?

12
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:22,916
{\an8}Hey!

13
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:24,959
{\an8}What are you looking at?

14
00:01:25,835 --> 00:01:27,629
{\an8}- Nothing.
- That's why.

15
00:01:27,712 --> 00:01:29,172
{\an8}You don't want fish and chips.

16
00:01:29,255 --> 00:01:31,800
{\an8}You want chicks!

17
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:34,636
{\an8}Mikoy…

18
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:39,682
{\an8}Let's talk. Man to man.

19
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:41,976
{\an8}That got serious all of a sudden.

20
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:44,771
{\an8}Are you drunk? It's just juice.

21
00:01:47,398 --> 00:01:48,691
{\an8}Okay.

22
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:51,402
{\an8}Let's just talk
man to man, seriously, okay?

23
00:01:51,486 --> 00:01:52,821
{\an8}- Okay.
- Listen.

24
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:53,780
{\an8}All right.

25
00:01:56,491 --> 00:02:01,162
{\an8}I just want you to know
that Alex is risking everything

26
00:02:01,246 --> 00:02:02,247
{\an8}just to be here.

27
00:02:03,498 --> 00:02:04,791
{\an8}For you.

28
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:06,793
{\an8}Okay?

29
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:10,588
{\an8}And now that they've met, we've all met,

30
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:12,465
{\an8}she now has a face to Chiara.

31
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:15,885
{\an8}And now that she has Chiara's face,

32
00:02:15,969 --> 00:02:20,140
{\an8}soon she'll have a face
to the whole syndicate.

33
00:02:20,723 --> 00:02:23,351
{\an8}And if ever

34
00:02:23,893 --> 00:02:27,105
{\an8}Alex's identity gets exposed
to the syndicate,

35
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:29,107
{\an8}consider her dead.

36
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:31,359
{\an8}Because Viktor won't be happy.

37
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:39,993
{\an8}Alex really trusts you. A lot.

38
00:02:40,702 --> 00:02:42,996
{\an8}But don't get me wrong.

39
00:02:43,079 --> 00:02:44,747
{\an8}I understand you love Chiara.

40
00:02:45,498 --> 00:02:48,543
{\an8}But we need to do the right thing here

41
00:02:48,626 --> 00:02:50,879
{\an8}because we have a mission to accomplish.

42
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:55,425
{\an8}Hey, do you understand me?

43
00:02:56,885 --> 00:02:59,596
{\an8}Okay. I'm saying all of this to you,

44
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:01,973
{\an8}because if there ever comes a point

45
00:03:02,056 --> 00:03:05,685
{\an8}where I have to choose who to save
between the two of you,

46
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:08,771
my answer won't change.

47
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:10,857
I understand.

48
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,452
You don't have anything to worry about.

49
00:03:25,663 --> 00:03:27,290
Mikoy loves you very much.

50
00:03:33,796 --> 00:03:35,882
You're always the one
he keeps talking about.

51
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:40,845
From the moment he met you in Prague,

52
00:03:41,763 --> 00:03:44,265
until you came with him
here to the Philippines,

53
00:03:44,849 --> 00:03:47,185
he can't stop talking about the fact that,

54
00:03:47,268 --> 00:03:49,938
even though you come
from different social classes,

55
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:52,023
you never looked down on him.

56
00:03:53,358 --> 00:03:56,945
And your family welcomed him
with open arms.

57
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:05,536
A man who will sacrifice everything
for the person he loves.

58
00:04:06,162 --> 00:04:09,540
And one day, if there ever comes a point

59
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:11,876
where you have doubts in him,

60
00:04:12,961 --> 00:04:17,048
always remember,
he stopped a bullet for you.

61
00:04:19,842 --> 00:04:23,680
Because if I have to choose
between Park Seo-joon and Mikoy,

62
00:04:24,889 --> 00:04:29,352
I will always choose the guy
who can protect me with all his heart.

63
00:04:29,435 --> 00:04:30,478
Right?

64
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:42,156
Mikoy!

65
00:04:42,907 --> 00:04:44,784
- You took so long.
- Oh my gosh.

66
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,160
You know what? Take care of Chiara.

67
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,419
Let's do this more often.

68
00:04:57,046 --> 00:04:59,590
I'm already sick of seeing
those two idiots' faces.

69
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:04,012
- Okay.
- Let's order.

70
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:05,346
- Go ahead.
- Fish and chips?

71
00:08:58,037 --> 00:08:58,871
I don't drink anymore.

72
00:08:59,455 --> 00:09:00,498
Yes.

73
00:09:09,882 --> 00:09:11,008
Yes.

74
00:09:11,676 --> 00:09:13,427
Guys, excuse me.

75
00:09:13,511 --> 00:09:14,762
- Sure, sure.
- Okay.

76
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:23,229
What's the problem, sir?

77
00:09:23,312 --> 00:09:25,606
Something happened to Vicek!

78
00:09:41,122 --> 00:09:44,166
My cat is vomiting yellow.

79
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:48,212
It's okay, I understand.
I used to be a "meow-my", too.

80
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:50,172
I also had a cat, so it's okay.

81
00:09:54,176 --> 00:09:58,097
Wow, the night is just starting.
We were just dancing with Mikoy.

82
00:10:00,349 --> 00:10:02,810
Uh… Okay.

83
00:10:02,893 --> 00:10:04,645
Maybe we'll crash otherwise.

84
00:10:04,729 --> 00:10:05,980
- She's a bit drunk.
- Yes, right.

85
00:10:06,063 --> 00:10:07,648
I'll just come with you.

86
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:09,817
- Okay, okay.
- I'm a bit drunk too, guys.

87
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:10,901
- Okay.
- Till next time.

88
00:10:10,985 --> 00:10:12,069
- See you again.
- Take care.

89
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:14,655
- Thank you so much! Bye!
- Nice to meet you!

90
00:10:14,739 --> 00:10:16,699
- Bye, Chiara!
- Bye!

91
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:26,125
Oh…

92
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:56,405
Sir, what happened?

93
00:10:56,947 --> 00:10:59,867
{\an8}NORBERTO S. RUIZ
GENERAL

94
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,996
What? How did that happen?

95
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:08,125
Sorry, it's late already.

96
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:09,835
I just want to ask, are you even sure?

97
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:13,589
Maybe he just went out to take a walk.
Maybe he went clubbing or something.

98
00:11:13,672 --> 00:11:16,509
I was ordered to assist Vicek.

99
00:11:16,592 --> 00:11:21,097
So I went to his hotel earlier
to check if he needed anything.

100
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:27,228
<i>Whoever did this, he's a professional.</i>

101
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:32,400
La Fornarina.

102
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:45,347
Where is the target?

103
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:04,617
Maybe his wife or child is there.

104
00:13:05,326 --> 00:13:07,286
They don't need to be involved.

105
00:13:14,793 --> 00:13:16,629
I've got this.

106
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:22,718
What information do you have on him?

107
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:24,261
What does he know now?

108
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:35,314
Leave it to me.

109
00:13:57,753 --> 00:13:59,838
{\an8}Whatever angle you look at it,

110
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:02,216
{\an8}it looks like the Valtrovis
already have him.

111
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:10,724
Vicek knows that Mikoy is our asset.

112
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:12,601
And I'm sure Viktor will force him

113
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:15,229
to extract whatever information
he can from him.

114
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:09,194
- Mom.
- Mikoy, dear!

115
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:13,115
You know, too bad,
your father just called.

116
00:17:13,198 --> 00:17:14,616
Oh, how is he?

117
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,744
He always asks about you.

118
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:20,372
He even said, "How is he doing?
Is he able to move now?"

119
00:17:20,456 --> 00:17:23,125
I told him you can already do
all your normal activities.

120
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:24,376
Right?

121
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:28,088
Then he even laughed. He was shocked!

122
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:31,216
Because I already told him
you went out with Chiara.

123
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:33,719
Where is Chiara?

124
00:17:34,344 --> 00:17:35,846
She went back to the mansion, Mom.

125
00:17:36,388 --> 00:17:38,432
Her father texted. There's an emergency.

126
00:17:38,515 --> 00:17:40,476
I hope she's okay.

127
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:41,602
Yes, she'll be fine, Mom.

128
00:17:41,685 --> 00:17:44,605
Chiara texted me too.
She said everything's okay.

129
00:17:44,688 --> 00:17:46,982
Dear, is there really no problem?

130
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:49,651
Yes. There's nothing, Mom.

131
00:17:50,277 --> 00:17:55,783
Because I talked to your father
before he left.

132
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:59,369
Don't take it the wrong way.

133
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:02,372
About Chiara's family.

134
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:08,754
{\an8}Of course, dear, we know
that a very big mess happened.

135
00:18:08,837 --> 00:18:12,007
{\an8}So, your father is a bit concerned.

136
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:18,347
The old man keeps asking
if you're really safe with the Valtrovis.

137
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:21,600
Mom…

138
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:24,478
Nothing bad is going to happen to me.

139
00:18:26,647 --> 00:18:28,649
I think God really loves me.

140
00:18:28,732 --> 00:18:29,817
Look at me.

141
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:34,696
- Until now, I'm still alive.
- I'm telling you, dear.

142
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:36,698
Don't treat it like a joke.

143
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:39,868
{\an8}Because your father and I
won't be able to take it

144
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:43,330
if something bad happens to you again.

145
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:46,834
Yes, Mom.

146
00:19:53,817 --> 00:19:55,360
<i>Vicek is missing.</i>

147
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:01,116
The Czech asset is missing?

148
00:20:11,001 --> 00:20:15,130
<i>Do you know how hard it is</i>
<i>to deal with the Czechs?</i>

149
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:17,966
I'm on full-time offense
just to convince them

150
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:19,927
to cooperate with us.

151
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:22,554
<i>And now their man is missing.</i>

152
00:20:22,638 --> 00:20:26,099
What if I don't get invited
to the European forum

153
00:20:26,183 --> 00:20:30,979
<i>on unified publishing,</i>
<i>intelligence exchange, counter terrorism,</i>

154
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:35,525
organized crime suppression,
and administrative synergy?

155
00:20:35,609 --> 00:20:40,072
<i>Do you know how fancy their buffet is?</i>

156
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:41,657
Huh!

157
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:46,036
What if I don't get invited next year?

158
00:20:55,754 --> 00:20:58,966
<i>And if they kill that guy Vicek,</i>

159
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:02,135
that will be a diplomatic headache.

160
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:05,514
<i>And the Moraviano will</i>
<i>not just be your problem,</i>

161
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:08,725
but your position will be at risk.

162
00:21:43,719 --> 00:21:46,513
{\an8}NORBERTO S. RUIZ
GENERAL

163
00:21:57,316 --> 00:21:58,859
- Vicek is missing.
- <i>What?</i>

164
00:21:58,942 --> 00:22:00,819
Maybe he just went to Boracay.

165
00:22:01,403 --> 00:22:05,407
You know, sunbathing
while drinking coconut juice.

166
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:09,453
Vicek knows about you.

167
00:22:09,536 --> 00:22:11,872
<i>So, if he's in Viktor's hands,</i>

168
00:22:11,955 --> 00:22:15,125
<i>he can extract information about you,</i>
<i>compromising your position.</i>

169
00:22:15,208 --> 00:22:16,626
<i>And if that happens,</i>

170
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:18,920
you will be declared as a burned asset.

171
00:22:19,629 --> 00:22:22,007
Burned asset? What does that mean?

172
00:22:24,885 --> 00:22:26,803
So you need to be placed
in protective custody.

173
00:22:26,887 --> 00:22:29,222
Where? At your apartment?

174
00:22:29,765 --> 00:22:30,724
Do you have a hot shower?

175
00:22:33,852 --> 00:22:36,271
Then where? Hey, wait a second!

176
00:22:36,354 --> 00:22:38,940
Don't tell me it's at Sianong's! No way!

177
00:22:39,024 --> 00:22:41,651
Come on! Give me a little dignity.

178
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:45,113
Not here in the Philippines, but abroad.

179
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:45,989
{\an8}ALEXANDRIA CORTEZ
AGENT

180
00:22:46,073 --> 00:22:47,949
{\an8}Somewhere far from the Moravianos.

181
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:50,452
And you'll also need a new identity.

182
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:52,704
A new identity and a new life.

183
00:22:52,788 --> 00:22:53,830
Abroad?

184
00:22:54,623 --> 00:22:56,500
<i>No way, Agent Alex!</i>

185
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:59,169
I won't hide and change my identity!

186
00:22:59,252 --> 00:23:00,962
Who do you think I am, Casper?

187
00:23:01,046 --> 00:23:03,090
I can't just ghost my family!

188
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:04,633
Especially the people I love.

189
00:23:11,014 --> 00:23:13,934
If they got Vicek,
they can get you as well.

190
00:23:16,394 --> 00:23:18,105
Well, if it's true I've been exposed,

191
00:23:18,688 --> 00:23:21,316
I'd rather just face
whatever happens to me here.

192
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:23,610
Even if I have to go all out
against the Moravianos.

193
00:23:23,693 --> 00:23:27,030
<i>What I will never do is run and hide.</i>

194
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:30,408
I was born here in the Philippines.
And I will die here.

195
00:23:33,995 --> 00:23:34,996
Mikoy?

196
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:51,012
<i>We're practically best friends now.</i>

197
00:23:51,096 --> 00:23:53,515
<i>Be careful with nice people.</i>

198
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:56,560
- <i>They're the ones hiding dark secrets.</i>
- You talk too much.

199
00:23:56,643 --> 00:23:58,353
If you don't want to hype me up,
then don't!

200
00:23:58,436 --> 00:23:59,563
<i>Whatever!</i>

201
00:24:00,564 --> 00:24:03,441
My friend, they are asking
for you to resign.

202
00:24:11,491 --> 00:24:14,452
They said you had an emergency last night?

203
00:24:16,830 --> 00:24:17,789
<i>Vicek?</i>

